fields.title: Masala milk
fields.excerpt: Masala milk is slightly sweetened milk nourished with cardamom, nutmeg and saffron. Warm milk is very delicious and it can be good for breakfast, snack and also as a dessert. It stays in the refrigerator for one or two days.
fields.content:
Preparation time: 10 minutes

Cooking time: 10 minutes

Ingredients

  • 2 cups whole milk or low fat
  • 2 tablespoons of sugar to taste

 To make milk powder:

  • 1/4 cup almonds
  • 1/4 cup pistachios
  • 1/4 cup cashews
  •  2 teaspoons of cardamom powder
  • 1/4 teaspoon nutmeg powder
  • 1 teaspoon saffron

Instructions:

1. Add almonds, pistachios, cashews, cardamom powder, and saffron to a spice grinder and pulse it a few times to make a coarse powder. Store this masala milk powder in an airtight container.

2. Add almonds, pistachios, cashews, cardamom powder, and saffron to a spice grinder and pulse it a few times to make a coarse powder. Store this masala milk powder in an airtight container. Note: That recipe makes extra masala powder, around 6 to 8 servings.

3. Cook on medium heat until the milk comes to a rolling boil. Lower the heat and stir in 2 tablespoons of masala powder for each cup of milk. Allow the milk to simmer on low heat for 2 to 3 minutes.

4. Pour the milk into cups. Garnish with sliced pistachios and a few strings of saffron. Enjoy hot.

fields.title: Pineapple curry
fields.excerpt: Pineapple curry is a deliciously sweet sour tasting dish made with pineapple, coconut, mustard seeds and curd. The recipe originated from Kerala cuisine.
fields.content:
Preparation time: 10 minutes

Cooking time: 10 minutes


Ingredients

Ripe Pineapple-1 1/2 cup

Mustard seeds-1/2 tsp

Chilly Powder-1/2 tsp

Cumin seeds-1/4tsp

Turmeric Powder-1/4tsp

Green Chilly-2

Salt -to taste

Sugar-2tbsp or according to your taste

Curry Leaves-2strings

Dry Red chilly-2(chopped)

Grated coconut-1cup

Curd- 1/2 cup or according to the sourness of the curd

Coconut Oil-1tsp

Instructions

1. Peel the pineapple.. ..Cut out all the eyes carefully. Cut into slices. Remove the hard portion and cut into very small pieces

2. Cook pineapple with chilli powder, turmeric powder ,sugar ,salt and curry leaves in 1/4 cup of water..

3. Grind coconut along with mustard seeds , green chilli , 2 curry leaves and cumin to a fine paste.

4. Now add the coconut paste to the cooked pineapple .

5. Mix well and reduce the flame and cook for another 10 minutes..

6. Now add the yogurt and mix well.no need to boil ..

7. Check the salt and sugar.. adjust ..

8. Heat coconut oil in a pan and add mustard seeds when it splutter add dry red chilly and curry leaves and pour over the curry.

9. Close it and serve when it cools down ..

fields.title: Egg biriyani
fields.excerpt: Fragrant basmati rice cooked with aromatic biriyani spices, herbs and boiled eggs
fields.content:
Preparation time: 20 minutes

Cooking time: 25 minutes


Ingredients:

2 cups basmati rice

6 large eggs

2 tablespoons ghee

2 yellow onions medium, thinly spiced

1 teaspoon cumin seeds

1/2 teaspoon black peppercorns

1/2 teaspoon black peppercorns

2 bay leaves

2 teaspoons Kashmiri red chilli powder

1/2 teaspoon ground turmeric

2.5 teaspoons salt

1.5 teaspoons garam masala

1/2 cup yogurt

1.5 teaspoons ginger grated

1.5 teaspoons garlic minced

2 cups water

1/2 cup cilantro leaves

1/4 cup mint leaves

1 tomato

1 pinch saffron

Instructions:


 1. Rinse the rice and soak in 4 cups of water for 20 minutes. Drain all the water after 20 minutes.

2. While the rice is soaking hard boil the eggs. Add 1 cup of water to the Instant Pot. Place the trivet and place eggs on top of it. Close the Instant Pot lid with the pressure valve to sealing. Set the Instant Pot to pressure cook (hi) for 5 minutes. Allow 5 minutes of natural pressure release and then release the remaining pressure and open the Instant pot. Using a pair of heat-resistant mitts, carefully pick up the Instant Pot insert and place it in the sink. Run cold water for 2 minutes over the eggs or place them in an ice bath. Once the eggs are cool to handle, peel them. Make 3 shallow slits to the hard-boiled eggs and keep them aside.

3. Set the Instant Pot to saute mode and add ghee. Add onions and saute until they turn light golden brown, about 10 minutes. Take half of the onions out and reserve. Note: If you have an air fryer you can use it or perfect golden fried onions.

4. Deglaze the bottom of the pot to remove any browning from sauteeing the onions. Use 1 to 2 tablespoons of water to help remove any stuck browned bits as this will help the Instant Pot come to pressure properly and not show the dreaded "BURN".

5. Add cumin seeds, black peppercorns, bay leaves, and saute for a minute. Turn the Instant Pot off and add red chili powder, turmeric, salt, garam masala, ginger, garlic, mint, cilantro, tomatoes, and yogurt. Mix well once again deglazing the pot. 

6. Add eggs and mix coating the eggs with the spices. Add rice over and spread it evenly. Add water and stir gently making sure most of the rice is under liquids. Close the Instant Pot and turn the pressure valve to sealing. Pressure Cook (Low) for 5 minutes followed by 5 minutes natural pressure release. Release the remaining pressure and open the Instant Pot. Layer the reserved caramelized onions and saffron milk evenly on top. Garnish with remaining cilantro. Enjoy hot with a lemon wedge and raita.

7. To make the raita, whisk the yogurt in a medium bowl. Add onions, tomatoes, salt, sugar and mix well. Garnish with cilantro.

fields.title: Green peas potato curry
fields.excerpt: A simple and easy north indian cuisine curry or sabzi recipe prepared with basic ingredients like potatoes and green peas.
fields.content:
Preparation time: 10 minutes

Cooking time: 25 minutes


Ingredients:

4 tsp oil

1/2 inch cardamom

2 pods cardamom

1 tsp dry fenugreek leaves

1/2 tsp cumin/jeera

 1/2 tsp turmeric/haldi

1 tsp kashmiri chilli powder

1/2 tsp coriander powder

1 onion

1 tsp ginger garlic paste

2 tomato (finely chopped)

2 potatoes (finely chopped)

1 tsp salt

1/2 cup peas

1 cup water

1 green chilli

1/2 cup garam masala

2 tbsp coriander leaves (finely chopped)

Instructions:

1. Firstly, in a pressure cooker heat 4 tsp oil and saute inch cinnamon, 2 pods cardamom, 1 tsp kasuri methi, tsp cumin till it turns aromatic.

2. Now add in tsp turmeric, 1 tsp kashmiri red chilli powder and tsp coriander powder. saute on low flame for 30 seconds.

3. Further add 1 onion and saute well.

4.  Additionally add 1 tsp ginger garlic paste and saute well.

5. Now add 2 tomato and saute till the tomatoes turn soft and mushy.

6. Furthermore, add 2 potato cubed and 1 tsp salt.

7. Saute for a minute or more.

8. Further add cup peas, 1 cup water and 1 green chilli.

9. Mix well and pressure cook for 3 whistles or till potato gets cooked.

10. Once the pressure gets settled down, mash slightly adjusting consistency.

11.  Add in tsp garam masala and 2 tbsp coriander leaves. mix well.

12.  Finally, serve aloo matar recipe with rice or roti.
